verbs.description: incask (third-person singular simple present incasks, present participle incasking, simple past and past participle incasked)

entries.meaning: (transitive, archaic) To cover with a casque or as with a casque.
examples: And being demanded of that which was donc by Nayu and Curlus, Incasked if euer it was heard, that the seruants were suborned and admitted as witnesses to the death of their Masters
